    "plan_content": "Here is the complete plan for implementing the **Stepper** compound component.\n\n---\n\n## What will be built\n\n**4 new files:**\n1. `apps/v4/registry/bases/radix/ui/stepper.tsx`\n2. `apps/v4/registry/bases/base/ui/stepper.tsx` ← identical to (1), one import path differs\n3. `apps/v4/registry/bases/radix/examples/stepper-example.tsx`\n4. `apps/v4/registry/bases/base/examples/stepper-example.tsx` ← identical to (3), three import paths differ\n\n**4 registry entries added** (no component files touched):\n5. `radix/ui/_registry.ts` — insert `stepper` between `spinner` and `switch`\n6. `base/ui/_registry.ts` — same with base URLs\n7. `radix/examples/_registry.ts` — insert `stepper-example` between `spinner-example` and `switch-example`\n8. `base/examples/_registry.ts` — identical entry\n\n---\n\n## Component design\n\n**7 sub-components** as named exports (matching shadcn convention):\n\n| Component | Element | Role |\n|---|---|---|\n| `Stepper` | `<div>` | Root — owns controlled/uncontrolled state, provides context |\n| `StepperItem` | `<div>` | Per-step container — provides item-level context |\n| `StepperTrigger` | `<button>` | Clickable trigger — calls `onValueChange(step)` |\n| `StepperTitle` | `<p>` | Step label text |\n| `StepperDescription` | `<p>` | Step subtitle text |\n| `StepperSeparator` | `<div>` | Visual line between steps (sibling of `StepperItem`) |\n| `StepperPanel` | `<div>` | Content panel — renders `null` when inactive |\n\n**Two React contexts** (pattern from `sidebar.tsx` / `toggle-group.tsx`):\n- `StepperContext` — root-level: `value`, `onValueChange`, `orientation`\n- `StepperItemContext` — item-level: `step`, `isActive`, `isCompleted`, `isDisabled`\n\n**Orientation** uses `data-orientation` + Tailwind `group-data-horizontal/stepper:` and `group-data-vertical/stepper:` selectors (same pattern as Tabs).\n\n**API follows Tabs conventions**: `value` prop on `StepperItem` and `StepperPanel` matches `TabsTrigger`/`TabsContent`.\n\n---\n\n## 5 demo variants\n\n1. **Basic** — 3-step horizontal, titles only, `defaultValue={1}`\n2. **With Description** — titles + descriptions, `defaultValue={2}` to show completed/active/pending states\n3. **Vertical** — `orientation=\"vertical\"` with stacking items and a vertical separator bar\n4. **With Content** — fully controlled, `StepperPanel` swaps content, Back/Next buttons drive navigation\n5. **Disabled Step** — middle step non-interactive and visually dimmed",
